## Adding a Geometry Column to an Existing Table

If you have an existing table (e.g., `locations`) and want to add spatial support:

```sql
-- Add a geography column (uses WGS84 / EPSG:4326 — standard GPS coordinates)
ALTER TABLE locations
    ADD COLUMN geom GEOGRAPHY(Point, 4326);

-- Populate from existing lat/lng columns
UPDATE locations
SET geom = ST_MakePoint(lng, lat)::GEOGRAPHY;

-- Add a spatial index
CREATE INDEX idx_locations_geom ON locations USING GIST (geom);
```

Use `GEOGRAPHY` (not `GEOMETRY`) for GPS coordinates — it handles the spherical earth math correctly for distance queries.

