## Spring Boot / Hibernate Integration

### `build.gradle` dependency

```groovy
// Hibernate Spatial (included in hibernate-core 6.x, no extra dep needed for Spring Boot 3.x)
implementation 'org.hibernate.orm:hibernate-spatial:6.4.4.Final'

// PostGIS JDBC dialect
implementation 'net.postgis:postgis-jdbc:2023.1.0'
```

### `application.yml` dialect

```yaml
spring:
  jpa:
    properties:
      hibernate:
        dialect: org.hibernate.spatial.dialect.postgis.PostgisPG10Dialect
```

For Spring Boot 3.x / Hibernate 6.x, the dialect is auto-detected. You may not need to set it explicitly — test first.

### Entity Example

```java
import org.locationtech.jts.geom.Point;

@Entity
public class Location {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;

    @Column(columnDefinition = "geography(Point,4326)")
    private Point geom;  // org.locationtech.jts.geom.Point
}
```

Add the JTS geometry library:

```groovy
implementation 'org.locationtech.jts:jts-core:1.19.0'
```

